The '''1994 All-America college football team''' is composed of the following All-American Teams: [[Associated Press]], [[United Press International]], [[Football Writers Association of America]], [[American Football Coaches Association]], [[Walter Camp Foundation]], [[Scripps-Howard]], ''[[The Sporting News]]'' and ''[[Football News]]''.<ref>[http://www.afca.com/pdf3/68830.pdf?ATCLID=289547&SPSID=69273&SPID=7863&DB_OEM_ID=9300 American Football Coaches Association]{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.theacc.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/121598aaa.html |title=Associated Press |access-date=March 29, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120223170809/http://www.theacc.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/121598aaa.html |archive-date=February 23, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sportswriters.net/fwaa/awards/allamerica/alltime.pdf |title=Football Writers Association of America |access-date=March 29, 2009 |archive-date=March 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190304073432/http://www.sportswriters.net/fwaa/awards/allamerica/alltime.pdf |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>[http://www.sportingnews.com/archives/almanac/nfl/cfbamer.html The Sporting News] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090227143400/http://www.sportingnews.com/archives/almanac/nfl/cfbamer.html |date=February 27, 2009 }}</ref><ref>[http://waltercamp.org/index.php/teams_and_awards/ Walter Camp Foundation] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090330065940/http://waltercamp.org/index.php/teams_and_awards |date=March 30, 2009 }}</ref><ref>[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?_product=CR&z=CRGB&p_theme=cr&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EAFE89C95E32BC4&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM Football News]</ref>

The College Football All-America Team is an honor given annually to the best American college football players at their respective positions. The original usage of the term All-America seems to have been to such a list selected by football pioneer Walter Camp in the 1890s. The NCAA officially recognizes All-Americans selected by the AFCA, AP, FN, FWAA, TSN, UPI, and WCFF to determine Consensus All-Americans.<ref>{{cite web|title=Football Award Winners|publisher=National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA)|year=2016|access-date=December 16, 2023|page=3|url=http://fs.ncaa.org/Docs/stats/football_records/2016/awards.pdf}}</ref>

The Newspaper Enterprise Association (NEA), the oldest All-American college football selection at the time, also selected a team.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Siner |first1=Howard |title=Steve McNair 'most prolific' in history of collegiate play |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BeQyAAAAIBAJ&pg=PA10&dq=NEA+All-American+team+Football&article_id=5451,10049904&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjiyoyhqvCSAxVXMmIAHaJpDAwQ6AF6BAgGEAM#v=onepage&q=NEA%20All-American%20team%20Football&f=false |access-date=24 February 2026 |work=The Rockmart Journal |date=21 December 1994}}</ref>

